{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_14","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' configs/recipe_search.example.yaml\"","aggregated_output":"# Search space for the rapid recipe-search phase (codex/prompts/recipe_search.md).\n# The executor proposes/refines recipes within these bounds; each attempt is a SHORT bounded training\n# whose only job is to reveal whether structured-Portuguese BPB is decreasing. Stay on the small model.\nproject: slt-portuguese\nmode: recipe_search\nmodel:\n  id: roneneldan/TinyStories-8M\n  full_parameter_training: true\n  precision: fp32\ndata:\n  # OPUS-100 en-pt is small; for real per-attempt tokens pull a streaming slice of a larger PT corpus.\n  candidates: [Helsinki-NLP/opus-100, oscar-corpus/OSCAR-2301, cc100, mc4]\n  language: pt\n  fixed_validation_manifest: data/manifests/portuguese_validation.json   # held fixed across attempts\nattempt:\n  minutes_per_attempt: [5, 15]        # keep attempts short; prefer more attempts over longer ones\n  tokens_per_attempt: [10_000_000, 40_000_000]\n  checkpoint_at_end: true\nsearch_space:\n  learning_rate: [3.0e-5, 5.0e-5, 1.0e-4, 2.0e-4]\n  warmup_fraction: [0.0, 0.03, 0.1]\n  lr_schedule: [constant, cosine, linear_decay]\n  grad_clip: [0.0, 1.0]\n  weight_decay: [0.0, 0.01, 0.1]\n  global_batch_size: [32, 64]\nsuccess_criteria:\n  structured_pt_bpb_decreasing: true   # the learning signal\n  beats_shuffled_control: true         # structure, not noise memorization\n  stable: true                         # no divergence / NaNs\non_success: \"Stop and recommend continuing the winning recipe from its checkpoint; planner halts for operator greenlight.\"\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
